		"en": "Mini-Box M4-ATX intelligent DC-DC ATX power supply — one catalog entry: its identity (the `power_supply` archetype) AND how it is talked to (its usbhid slot). `manufacturer: Mini-Box` and `archetype: power_supply` are inherited from ./_defaults.yaml.\n\nThis medium is the COMPLETE protocol, as data: a gateway in any language reads it to drive the device — which USB device to open (transport.usb), how to poll it (link), and how to decode the 24-byte frame (fields). Verified against the upstream m4api C source (mini-box/m4atx, m4api.c):\n\n  • Poll: interrupt-write [0x81,0x00] to EP 0x01, interrupt-read 24 bytes from EP 0x81.\n  • A valid frame stamps 0x21 at byte 0; the firmware version is byte 23 (high nibble = major).\n  • Voltage bytes are firmware-scaled: major < 2 uses the V1 conversion table (the `legacy`\n    profile below), major >= 2 the V2 table (the base `scale`). Temperature is a signed\n    big-endian 16-bit °C at byte 12, firmware-independent.\n\nThese byte offsets / scales / endianness are read directly off m4GetDiag + the m4TypeConversions V1/V2 tables in m4api.c — defined once here so every consuming gateway (in any language) branches off the same definition instead of each re-encoding it.\n\nDiag fields: each field LINKS nowhere yet — carried RAW with a `label` (the same interim path chint/dtsu666 uses for un-attributed registers), pending a DC-rail/enclosure feature atom on the power_supply archetype. `scale` is the V2 conversion; `scale_overrides.legacy` the V1 one. Voltages print to 2 decimals, temperature to 0 (matching m4PrintVal in m4api.c).\n\nControl plane: the device's 47 settable parameters (m4ConfigFields in m4api.c), read/written by INDEX over the same endpoints as the diag poll. GET writes [0xa4,0xa1,index,length], reads 24 bytes (magic 0x31), value at byte 4; SET writes [0xa4,0xa0,index,length,val…] and the device echoes index+value. `scale` is the V2 conversion table; `scale_overrides.legacy` the V1 one (only the voltage types differ between firmwares). Names are the lowercased device field names; the digit-leading rail fields (12V_MAX…) become v12_*/v5_*/v33_* to be valid slugs and to match the diag labels. Voltages are in SI volts (unit omitted); timers carry a 0xffff=\"never\" sentinel. All read_write except `reset` (a write-only factory-reset action).\n"
